ken@chinook.halcyon.com (Ken Pizzini) writes:

>BBS does rely on the unproven assumption
>that factoring is hard.

Actually, it relies on the even stronger assumption that determining
whether an element is a quadratic residue (a square) modulo a Blum
integer.  This does require that factoring is hard but also that there
is no other way of determining quadratic reciduasity.

Hal Finney
